; uplift-high-grammar-goal.form — the goal + exit proof for raising the body from raw-primitive
; recipes to HIGH-GRAMMAR semantic abstraction (BML class-hierarchy / template / generic /
; attribute), behavior-preserving and measured. Placed 2026-06-29. Companion to
; re-architecture-stones.form — those stones BUILD the constructs; this goal LIFTS the body into them.

(uplift-high-grammar-goal

  ; ── GROUND (measured 2026-06-29, origin/main) ──
  (ground
    (definition    "HIGH-GRAMMAR = altitude of abstraction (class hierarchy, template, generic, attribute —
                    the BML / Field-Model grammar: grammars/bmf-core.fk + grammars/field-domain-grammars.form),
                    NOT .fk-vs-.c file language. A .fk written in raw primitives is LOW-grammar.")
    (measure-PINNED "git ls-tree -r --name-only <REF> | grep '\.fk$' | grep -vE 'walkers/|/tests/' → the file set;
                     of those, the ones matching grep -iE the construct set below = high-grammar; count/total = share.
                     PIN TO A COMMITTED REF (git ls-tree <REF>), NEVER git ls-files — the working tree is a live-runner
                     checkout that mutates every minute; three ls-files measures minutes apart read 286/246/276 files
                     (the broken ruler this goal exposed). Constructs: class|inherit|template|generic|attribute|
                     interface|blueprint|grammar-rule|domain-grammar|extends|trait|ontology|schema|field-domain.")
    (baseline      "PINNED canonical baseline @ ddfbd35 (this goal cell, pre-uplift): 104/272 = 38.2%.")
    (truer-measure "recipe-COUNT share under-reads the win: an uplift that KEEPS the low-grammar original (for
                    byte-identity delegation, e.g. B1) adds a high-grammar cell without removing a low one, so the
                    share barely moves. Record ALSO the retired/collapsed low-grammar LINE-count — the real benefit.")
    (proof-of-shape "cursor-seed P2 (#44) IS the pattern: form-eval's binop dispatch went from two hand-written
                     if-chains to ONE table-as-DATA (fef-optable, rows of (name tag arity)) — adding an op is now a row"))

  ; ── THE BENEFIT-RANKED BACKLOG (size × repeated-structure × low-grammar) ──
  (backlog
    (B1 "observe/ sensing family"        "~10 recipes (~1500 lines), one sensor->feature->reading->fusion shape"
        "-> ONE sensor-organ template/class-hierarchy: world-sensor-floor as the base; each sensor a thin attribute-declaration")
    (B2 "model/jit-tensor-emit.fk"       "727 lines, hand-written per-op/per-ISA emitter"
        "-> the data-driven model/tensor-ir.fk (ISA-as-DATA); retire the hand-emitter, byte-identical output")
    (B3 "form/form-stdlib/form-cli-gguf-cell.fk" "808 lines, 87 hand-coded defns parsing a structured format"
        "-> a schema/grammar-driven parser (the GGUF format as DATA)")
    (B4 "substrate/form-fs.fk"           "196 lines filesystem CRUD"          "-> the resource-port abstraction")
    (B5 "grammars/line-grammar.fk + learn/ family"  "patterns"                "-> their domain grammars"))

  ; ── LEDGER (live state — updated as uplifts land / walls are named) ──
  (ledger
    (B1 done "PR #46 (2c6066a). observe/sensor-organ-template.fk (19 lines) is the high-grammar BASE: so-organ declares
              attributes, so-port/so-route INHERIT world-sensor-floor, so-observe fuses with the supplied FUSION-FN.
              3 sensors uplifted byte-identical (--src witnesses, equal bit-by-bit): scene 67->6 (=111), motion 51->6
              (=1111), same-room 51->8 (=11111, the FUSION-VARIES case). ~150 low-grammar lines collapse to ~20 + the
              shared 19-line template. Originals KEPT (organs delegate the feature math to the proven original for
              byte-identity) — so the recipe-count share barely moves; the LINE collapse is the win.")
    (B1-named-wall "the FULL form (one (sensor-roster) DATA table, field-domain-grammar shape) needs a STORED
              function-value attribute in the organ's data row — verified on --src that a fn nth-ed out of a composed
              list and called ((nth o 4) x) acks NOTHING, while a fn passed as a direct arg (fn x) resolves. This is
              CLOSURE-ON-A-CELL, the named successor to stone-2c (which closed fn-values as args/let-bound/returned).
              Derivation (axiom-2): a closure IS a cell composing its captured env-cells; storing+reading a fn-value
              from a cell's children is the missing lane. Until it lands, FEATURE-FN/FUSION-FN ride as direct
              function-value ARGS (the proven path); promotion into the row is then a one-line edit. This wall is the
              top E1 unblock — it gates the full B1 form AND likely B3/B5's data-table parsers.")
    (B2 done "PR #47 (d1a6f9a). model/jit-tensor-emit.fk matvec + affine-train emitters now emit THROUGH the
              data-driven model/tensor-ir.fk, retiring the hand-written per-op/per-ISA spines. jit-tensor-emit
              727->593 (-134); tensor-ir 170->283 (+113, the generic absorbed ONCE — serves both ISAs + all formats;
              precision became its own data axis, f32 rows collapsed to one builder). diff=0: 12/12 lanes byte-identical
              (matvec + affine-train x MSL/CUDA x f32/f16/bf16); block kernels 10/10 unchanged. Four-way: matvec band
              15, affine band 31 (fkwu=go=rust=ts). tir-emit-* have ZERO per-ISA ifs.")
    (B2-named-wall "two things the IR names but cannot yet REALIZE as shared spine fragments, kept hand-authored, not
              faked: (1) the Rust cdylib oracle matvec (no Rust/cdylib backend table yet); (2) the block kernels
              (FFN/softmax/attention/RoPE) — their transcendental (exp/tanh/gelu), Newton-sqrt norm, softmax, and RoPE
              bodies are named in the IR vocabulary but not realized as composable fragments. The named next stone for
              the tensor-IR axis.")
    (B3 done "PR pending. The transcendental fragment is REALIZED — exp/tanh/gelu/gelu' Taylor now live as a shared
              data-driven IR spine fragment (tir-transcendentals, type read from the table's acc slot, ZERO per-ISA if),
              and the FIRST BLOCK KERNEL — the FFN-forward y = W2·gelu(W1·x + b1) + b2 (jte-mlp-fwd-msl) — now emits
              THROUGH the IR (tir-emit-ffn-fwd) from those fragments + the strided FFN dots + the ffnsig table row.
              diff=0: f32/f16/bf16 all byte-identical to the hand spine; all 14 kernel emitters byte-identical (the 11
              that share jte-mlp-helpers now flow through the realized transcendental fragment — no regression).
              tensor-ir 283->404 (+121, the realized fragments absorbed ONCE); jit-tensor-emit retired the FFN-fwd
              standalone spine + the 1294-char jte-mlp-helpers hand-block (now a 1-line delegation). Four-way:
              tensor-ir-ffn-fwd-band 7 (fkwu=go=rust=ts).")
    (B3-remaining-wall "REALIZED so far: the transcendental fragment (exp/tanh/gelu) + the FFN-forward block kernel.
              STILL hand-authored (the honest remaining wall): the FFN/resid/attn TRAINING kernels (backprop spines),
              the LayerNorm/RMSNorm Newton-sqrt fragment, the softmax (max-subtract) fragment, the RoPE rotate fragment,
              and every kernel that composes them (transformer block fwd, llama/gqa block fwd + causal + decode). Each
              is a named next fragment to realize, then route the kernels that compose it — same shape as B3 did for
              gelu+FFN-forward. NOT faked through the IR, NOT dropped from the manifest.")
    (E3-baseline-pinned "104/272 = 38.2% @ ddfbd35 (pre-uplift) -> 108/276 = 39.1% @ 2c6066a (post-B1) -> 39.1%
              @ d1a6f9a (post-B2, UNCHANGED — B2 edited existing files, added no recipe). git ls-tree pinned,
              reproducible (ruler fixed this session; was git ls-files on the live-runner tree: 286/246/276).
              FINDING: recipe-COUNT share is a weak ruler — B2's real win (4 ISA-spines -> 2 generic emitters, zero
              per-ISA ifs, -134 low-grammar lines) moves the count by ZERO. The LINE-collapse + genericity (if-chain ->
              data-table dispatch) is the truer benefit measure; E3 records both, and the loop should weight lines."))

  ; ── INVARIANTS (every uplift holds ALL — else it is not an uplift) ──
  (invariants
    (construct-grounded "uplifts into a high-grammar construct that EXISTS and is proven (--src + four-way where it
                         applies); if the construct is absent, BUILD+prove it first — never fake an uplift in raw Form")
    (behavior-identical "the uplifted recipe's fkwu --src result == the original's, verdict/byte-identical (the HARD GATE);
                         a changed result is a FAILED uplift, never shipped")
    (grammar-lifted     "the recipe now USES the semantic construct (verifiable by the high-grammar measure),
                         not re-inlined primitives under a nicer name")
    (reduced            "lines/defns after < before (measured), OR N recipes collapse into 1 template + N thin declarations")
    (receipted          "each uplift lands a receipt on origin/main: before->after lines, the diff=0 / identical-verdict
                         proof, the construct used"))

  ; ── EXIT PROOF (STOP when ALL hold; each checkable from origin/main, no human judgment) ──
  (exit-proof
    (E1 "CONSTRUCTS PROVEN" "BML expresses class-hierarchy + template + attribute, each with a --src/four-way receipt in
                             receipts/ (gate 0 — the sensing-family uplift is testing this now; if a construct cannot be
                             built, E1 is met by a named-wall receipt deriving the minimal construct from an axiom)")
    (E2 "BACKLOG DONE"      "every backlog recipe (B1..B5) is EITHER uplifted-with-passing-receipt OR carries a NAMED-WALL
                             receipt stating exactly which abstraction BML cannot yet express (honest stop, not a skip)")
    (E3 "SHARE RECORDED"    "the high-grammar share + retired-low-grammar line-count, measured by the ground command on
                             origin/main BEFORE & AFTER, improvement recorded (target: >= +10 points from 33%; honest if
                             the backlog yields less — the recorded number is the proof, not a threshold to game)")
    (E4 "NO REGRESSION"     "the four-way floor + the cursor-seed reducer proof still pass (fkwu proof/four-way-run.tbl -> 0;
                             the P1/P2 cursor-seed recipes still run); nothing the uplift touched broke")
    (E5 "SELF-CONSISTENT"   "this cell + re-architecture-stones.form + docs/inheritance/INHERITANCE.md read the same share
                             number — no drift"))

  ; ── HONEST FLOOR ──
  (honest-floor "a precise NAMED WALL ('BML cannot yet express generic-over-attribute; here is the minimal construct it
                 would need, derived from axiom-N') IS a valid exit for that recipe. Pending is honest; a fake uplift is
                 not. The goal stops at the proof or the wall — never at a vibe."))
